description: Manage outbound endpoint with dns resolver.

commands.name: az dns-resolver outbound-endpoint create
commands.summary: Create an outbound endpoint for a DNS resolver.
commands.syntax:
az dns-resolver outbound-endpoint create --dns-resolver-name
                                         --id
                                         --name
                                         --resource-group
                                         [--if-match]
                                         [--if-none-match]
                                         [--location]
                                         [--no-wait {0, 1, f, false, n, no, t, true, y, yes}]
                                         [--tags]

commands.name: az dns-resolver outbound-endpoint delete
commands.summary: Deletes an outbound endpoint for a DNS resolver. WARNING: This operation cannot be undone.
commands.syntax:
az dns-resolver outbound-endpoint delete [--dns-resolver-name]
                                         [--ids]
                                         [--if-match]
                                         [--name]
                                         [--no-wait {0, 1, f, false, n, no, t, true, y, yes}]
                                         [--resource-group]
                                         [--subscription]
                                         [--yes]

commands.name: az dns-resolver outbound-endpoint list
commands.summary: Lists outbound endpoints for a DNS resolver.

commands.name: az dns-resolver outbound-endpoint show
commands.summary: Gets properties of an outbound endpoint for a DNS resolver.

commands.name: az dns-resolver outbound-endpoint update
commands.summary: Updates an outbound endpoint for a DNS resolver.
commands.syntax:
az dns-resolver outbound-endpoint update [--add]
                                         [--dns-resolver-name]
                                         [--force-string {0, 1, f, false, n, no, t, true, y, yes}]
                                         [--ids]
                                         [--if-match]
                                         [--name]
                                         [--no-wait {0, 1, f, false, n, no, t, true, y, yes}]
                                         [--remove]
                                         [--resource-group]
                                         [--set]
                                         [--subscription]
                                         [--tags]

commands.name: az dns-resolver outbound-endpoint wait
commands.summary: Place the CLI in a waiting state until a condition is met.
